<TITLE> Myanmar sets constitutional referendum for May 10 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 YANGON. April 9 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Myanmar's military government has scheduled a referendum on an army-drafted constitution for May 10, state television said on Wednesday. Ccpies of the charter -- which Western governments have dismissed as a sham to entrench more than four decades of military rule -- would go on sale immediately, the announcement also said.
